---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<div class="breaking-news-banner">
				<span class="pulse">BREAKING</span>
				<span class="news-ticker">Mysterious Streamer Bitter Lizus Sigma's Identity Confirmed</span>
			</div>

			<div class="featured-news">
				<div class="news-meta">
					<span class="category">GAMING</span>
					<span class="timestamp">Updated 2 hours ago</span>
				</div>
				<h1>Gaming Community Stunned: Bitter Lizus Sigma's True Identity Revealed</h1>
				<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1542751371-adc38448a05e?w=1200&auto=format&fit=crop&q=60" alt="Gaming Setup" class="hero-image">
				<div class="byline">By NetRunner, Lead Gaming Correspondent</div>
				
				<p class="lead">
					In an unprecedented turn of events, the true identity of the legendary Paladins streamer known as 
					"Bitter Lizus Sigma" has been confirmed, ending years of speculation within the gaming community.
				</p>

				<div class="article-content">
					<p>
						The enigmatic streamer, who has captivated audiences with exceptional Paladins gameplay and 
						maintained complete anonymity for years, has become a central figure in the game's community, 
						known for achieving the highest rank while never revealing their face or real identity.
					</p>

					<div class="key-points">
						<h3>Key Revelations</h3>
						<ul>
							<li>Unprecedented 98% win rate in competitive Paladins matches</li>
							<li>Revolutionary strategies that transformed the game's meta</li>
							<li>Mysterious disappearances during major tournaments</li>
							<li>Cryptic messages in stream titles that sparked community theories</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<blockquote>
						"Bitter Lizus Sigma isn't just a streamer; they're a phenomenon that has redefined what's 
						possible in Paladins," says Pro Player Marcus "VortexKing" Thompson.
					</blockquote>

					<h3>Community Impact</h3>
					<p>
						The streamer's influence extends beyond gameplay, creating a mysterious persona that has 
						spawned countless theories and investigations within the gaming community. Their signature 
						style of communication through morse code donations and encrypted chat messages has created 
						a dedicated following of code-breakers and gaming enthusiasts.
					</p>
				</div>

				<!-- Comments Section -->
				<div class="comments-section">
					<h3>Community Discussion</h3>
					<div class="comment">
						<div class="comment-header">
							<span class="comment-author">CyberSlayer99</span>
							<span class="comment-time">2 hours ago</span>
						</div>
						<p>This has to be the biggest revelation in gaming history! The strategies they introduced changed everything!</p>
					</div>
					<div class="comment">
						<div class="comment-header">
							<span class="comment-author">QuantumGamer</span>
							<span class="comment-time">1 hour ago</span>
						</div>
						<p>I still can't believe the AI theory turned out to be true. The patterns were there all along!</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="related-stories">
				<h2>Related Coverage</h2>
				<div class="story-grid">
					<a href="/blog/paladins-meta" class="story-card">
						<span class="category">ANALYSIS</span>
						<h4>How Bitter Lizus Changed Paladins Meta Forever</h4>
						<p>An in-depth look at revolutionary strategies...</p>
					</a>
					<a href="/blog/community-theories" class="story-card">
						<span class="category">COMMUNITY</span>
						<h4>Top 5 Theories About Bitter Lizus Identity</h4>
						<p>From pro player to AI: Community speculations...</p>
					</a>
					<a href="/blog/streaming-impact" class="story-card">
						<span class="category">IMPACT</span>
						<h4>The Rise of Mystery Gaming Personalities</h4>
						<p>How anonymous streamers are changing gaming...</p>
					</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 1200px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 0 1em;
	}
	.breaking-news-banner {
		background: var(--accent-dark);
		color: white;
		padding: 0.5em 1em;
		margin: 1em 0;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1em;
		border-radius: 4px;
	}
	.pulse {
		background: #ff4444;
		padding: 0.2em 0.5em;
		border-radius: 3px;
		animation: pulse 2s infinite;
	}
	@keyframes pulse {
		0% { opacity: 1; }
		50% { opacity: 0.5; }
		100% { opacity: 1; }
	}
	.news-ticker {
		font-weight: 500;
	}
	.featured-news {
		background: white;
		padding: 2em;
		border-radius: 8px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
		margin: 2em 0;
	}
	.news-meta {
		display: flex;
		gap: 1em;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}
	.category {
		background: var(--accent);
		color: white;
		padding: 0.2em 0.5em;
		border-radius: 3px;
		font-size: 0.9em;
		font-weight: 500;
	}
	.timestamp {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}
	.hero-image {
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 1000px;
		margin: 1em 0;
		border-radius: 8px;
	}
	.byline {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-style: italic;
		margin-bottom: 1em;
	}
	.lead {
		font-size: 1.2em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		font-weight: 500;
		margin-bottom: 1.5em;
	}
	.key-points {
		background: rgb(var(--gray-light), 0.3);
		padding: 1.5em;
		border-radius: 8px;
		margin: 1.5em 0;
	}
	.key-points ul {
		margin-top: 0.5em;
		padding-left: 1.5em;
	}
	blockquote {
		border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
		padding: 1em;
		margin: 1.5em 0;
		background: rgb(var(--gray-light), 0.3);
	}
	.comments-section {
		margin-top: 3em;
		padding-top: 2em;
		border-top: 1px solid rgb(var(--gray-light));
	}
	.comment {
		margin: 1.5em 0;
		padding: 1em;
		background: rgb(var(--gray-light), 0.2);
		border-radius: 8px;
	}
	.comment-header {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		margin-bottom: 0.5em;
	}
	.comment-author {
		font-weight: 600;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
	}
	.comment-time {
		font-size: 0.9em;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
	}
	.related-stories {
		margin: 2em 0;
	}
	.story-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
		gap: 1.5em;
		margin-top: 1em;
	}
	.story-card {
		background: white;
		padding: 1.5em;
		border-radius: 8px;
		box-shadow: var(--box-shadow);
		text-decoration: none;
		color: inherit;
		transition: transform 0.2s;
	}
	.story-card:hover {
		transform: translateY(-3px);
	}
	.story-card h4 {
		margin: 0.5em 0;
		color: var(--accent-dark);
	}
	.story-card p {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin: 0;
	}
	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.story-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>